    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nAn already defined variable gets overwritten if the same name is used as a placeholder in list comprehension, while in original python code this does not happen.\r\nPossibly the same problem as #1159, but I thought it might be worth it to create a new issue for this specific case because the error is hard to notice since there is no indication this happened.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\n\r\ncode of cython_test.pyx file\r\n```\r\nvariable = 'variable'\r\nunrelated_list = ['listentry1', 'listentry2', 'listentry3']\r\nfiltered_list = [variable.upper() for variable in unrelated_list]\r\nprint('variable is:' + variable)\r\n```\r\nsetup.py:\r\n```\r\nimport distutils.core\r\nimport Cython.Build\r\ndistutils.core.setup(\r\n    ext_modules = Cython.Build.cythonize(\"cython_test.pyx\"))\r\n```\r\nfinaly python code analog to .pyx file:\r\n```\r\nprint('Now cython code is imported, variable will be printed:')\r\nimport cython_test\r\n\r\nprint('Now python code is run exactly as in pyx file:')\r\n# from here on the code is exactly the same as in the .pyx file\r\nvariable = 'variable'\r\nunrelated_list = ['listentry1', 'listentry2', 'listentry3']\r\nfiltered_list = [variable.upper() for variable in unrelated_list]\r\nprint('variable is:' + variable)\r\n```\r\nProduces:\r\n```\r\nNow cython code is imported, variable will be printed:\r\nvariable is:listentry3\r\nNow python code is run exactly as in pyx file:\r\nvariable is:variable\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nBehavoir of cython compiled code to match python code behavoir. Otherwise give warning while compilation.\r\n\r\n**Environment (please complete the following information):**\r\n - OS: Windows 10\r\n - Python version: 3.9.3\r\n - Cython version: 0.29.22\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nSorry if this is an already known bug, I am 90% sure I made a mistake somewhere\r\n",
