            "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
            "body": "This is expected behaviour in Python 2. Note that Python 0.29.22 follows Python 2 behaviour by default when compiling pyx files (even when running in Python 3). You can change this with Cython's `language_level` parameter.\r\n\r\n```\r\n#cython: language_level=3\r\n```\r\n(or `3str`).\r\n\r\nEdit: relevant link http://python-history.blogspot.com/2010/06/from-list-comprehensions-to-generator.html",
